<paragraph id="87463686B0388806FF7AFBDB99A970E6" blockId="6.[166,1225,1071,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="477">Hosts: American bison (P = 45.5 %; I = 21.2 (2–86)); common eland (P = 86.8 %; I = 268.5 (1–2,470)); saiga antelope (P = 21.7 %; I = 1.6 (1–3)); blue wildebeest (P = 100 %; I = 5); markhor (P = 36.7 %; I = 8.3 (2–16)); Barbary sheep (P = 40 %; I = 9.5 (3–16)); sitatunga (P = 33.3 %; I = 5); guanaco (P = 33.3 %; I = 4); llama (P = 33.3 %; I = 1).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="87463686B0388806FF7AFB5B98BC70C6" blockId="6.[166,1225,1071,1258]" box="[219,739,1231,1258]" pageId="6" pageNumber="477">Site of infection: abomasum, small intestine.</paragraph>
